---
title: "Why Professional Services Firms Outgrow SaaS Before They Realize It"
date: "2024-09-25"
summary: "Professional services firms outgrow SaaS tools faster than they expect. Know the signs and plan the transition."
coverImage: ""
tags:
  - "Professional Services"
author: "Redevise"
---

Your firm uses off-the-shelf SaaS tools. They worked for 10 consultants. At 30 consultants, they are breaking. The tools were not built for your [workflows](/process).

Professional services firms have unique [workflows](/process). Project-based work. Client-specific processes. Utilization tracking. The SaaS tools are built for generic businesses. The gap grows as the firm grows.

Here are the signs you have outgrown SaaS.

Workarounds exceed 20 percent of workflows. If more than 20 percent of your work happens outside the tools, the tools are not enough.

Data is manually reconciled. If someone is copying data between systems every week, the systems are not connected. The connection is the problem.

Reporting requires manual compilation. If a report requires data from three systems and manual compilation, the tools are not serving you.

I consulted for a professional services firm in 2024. The firm had 40 consultants. They were using generic SaaS tools. The workarounds were 35 percent of workflows. We built custom tools. The workarounds dropped to 8 percent. The administrative time dropped 45 percent.

The teams that do not recognize the signs are the ones that stay on broken tools. The teams that recognize are the ones that transition.

Measure the workarounds. Check the reconciliation. Check the reporting. If the signs are present, you have outgrown SaaS.
